This paper deals with capacity bounds for waveform channels, which are typically studied in the information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SP) communities. The use of square-law detection is also a common topic in these fields. The paper also involves some statistical inference (cs.SI) and machine learning (cs.MM) techniques. Finally, the paper presents theoretical results and bounds, which are often studied in the machine learning (cs.LG) community.
